<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,582,1867]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,267,654,679]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">Adult</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[286,424,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 22 – 42" captionStartId="10.[151,264,1704,1727]" captionTargetBox="[243,1339,185,1683]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[243,1344,173,1694]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 22 – 42. Adults of Istrianis species. 22 — I. kravchenkoi, ♂, HT, Palestine (gen. slide 5699, H. Hendriksen); 23 — I. wachtlii, ♂, Palestine (gen. slide 37 / 11, O. Bidzilya); 24 — I. wachtlii, ♀, Egypt (gen. slide 62 / 10, O. Bidzilya); 25 — I. brucinella, ♀, Egypt (gen. slide 266 / 12, O. Bidzilya); 26 — I. brucinella, ♀, Pakistan; 27 — I. sattleri, ♂, HT, Pakistan (B. M. gen. slide 14355); 28 — I. sattleri, ♂, PT, Pakistan (gen. slide 413 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 29 — I. armatus, ♂, HT, Yemen (gen. slide 567 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 30 — I. armatus, ♀, PT, Yemen (gen. slide 568 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 31 — I. femoralis, ♂, Kyrgyzstan; 32 — I. lvovskyi, HT, ♂, Mongolia (gen. slide 63 / 10, O. Bidzilya); 33 — I. lvovskyi, ♂, PT, Mongolia (gen. slide 252 / 12, O. Bidzilya); 34 — I. lvovskyi, PT, ♂, Mongolia; 35 — I. sruogai, PT, ♂, Tadzhikistan; 36 — I. sruogai, PT, ♀, Tadzhikistan (gen. slide 178 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 37 — I. piskunovi, HT, ♂, Ukraine (GU 96 / 630, P. Huemer); 38 — I. falkovitshi, HT, ♂, Turkmenistan (gen. slide 257 / 12, O. Bidzilya); 39 — I. falkovitshi, PT, ♀, Turkmenistan (gen. slide 10 / 13, O. Bidzilya); 40 — I. squamodorella, LT, ♂, Palestine (gen. slide 26 / 11, O. Bidzilya); 41 — I. squamodorella, PT, ♀, Palestine (gen. slide 26 / 11, O. Bidzilya); 42 — I. squamodorella, PT, ♀, Palestine." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237392/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">Figs 38, 39</figureCitation>
). Wingspan 
<quantity box="[570,740,655,679]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.045" metricValueMax="1.0699999999999998" metricValueMin="1.02" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" unit="mm" value="10.45" valueMax="10.7" valueMin="10.2">10.2–10.7 mm</quantity>
. Head, thorax and tegulae covered with white, black-tipped scales, frons nearly white, labial palpus white with black basal and medial rings, upper side of segment 
<number box="[1304,1318,691,715]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" value="2.0">2</number>
off-white; scape white, densely mottled with black, other antennal segments black with white basal rings. Forewing covered with grey, black tipped scales, a small white spot of irregular shape just beyond the middle of costal margin, diffuse white spot at ¾ of costa, a few black raised scales surrounded by yellowish orange about 
<number box="[1236,1246,799,823]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1257,1271,799,823]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" value="3.0">3</number>
near dorsum; elongated yellow sub-costal streak from base to ¼, a small yellowish orange subcostal spot in middle and one such spot in the end of cell, two small orange dots at 
<number box="[687,699,871,895]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" value="3.0">3</number>
/ 
<number box="[709,723,871,895]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" value="4.0">4</number>
length; base and subapical area mottled with white; cilia white, black-tipped; hindwing of male light brown except for white area from base to nearly half length, hindwing of female light grey.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,582,1867]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">
Variation. The female 
<typeStatus box="[456,552,979,1003]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">paratype</typeStatus>
has lighter, almost entirely white head, forewings almost uniformly blackish grey, and the yellowish pattern poorly expressed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="435" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,582,1867]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,370,1050,1075]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[386,472,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 75 – 80" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1527,1550]" captionTargetBox="[311,1269,205,1486]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[311,1275,193,1507]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 75 – 80. Male genitalia of Istrianis species. 75 — I. piskunovi, HT, Ukraine (gen. slide 96 / 630, P. Huemer); 76 — I. falkovitshi, HT, Turkmenistan (gen. slide 257 / 12, O. Bidzilya); 77 — I. squamodorella, LT, Middle East (gen. slide 26 / 11); 78 — I. nigrosquamella, HT, Iran (gen. slide 317 / 14); 79 — I. kyrgyzsquamella, HT, Kyrgyzstan (gen. slide 58 / 11); 80 — I. yemeniasquamella, PT, Yemen (gen. slide 223 / 12, O. Bidzilya)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237399/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">
Fig. 
<number box="[440,472,1050,1075]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" value="76.0">76</number>
</figureCitation>
). Distal portion of tergite VIII tongue-shaped, nearly parallel-sided, lateral arms very narrow, anteromedial emargination deep, distal portion subrectangular; sternite VIII more than two times longer than broad, posteriolateral projections moderately narrow; uncus slender, tapered, slightly narrower than gnathos; gnathos distinctly longer than uncus, apex with strongly sclerotized hook; tegumen boomerang-shaped, lateral lobes narrow, weakly constricted medially; valva moderately broadened in distal half; phallus tapered distally, slightly longer than valva.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,582,1867]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,400,1266,1291]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[418,522,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 99 – 101" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1890,1913]" captionTargetBox="[344,1251,519,1851]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[323,1264,517,1869]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 99 – 101. Female genitalia of Istrianis species. 99 — I. sruogai, Turkmenistan (gen. slide 178 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 100 — I. piskunovi, PT, Ukraine (gen. slide 92 / 11, O. Bidzilya); 101 — I. falkovitshi, PT, Turkmenistan (gen. slide 10 / 13, O. Bidzilya)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237407/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">
Figs 
<number box="[478,522,1267,1291]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" value="101131.0">101</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[538,583,1267,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 126 – 140" captionStartId="42.[151,264,1729,1752]" captionTargetBox="[261,1313,203,1673]" captionTargetId="figure@42.[249,1329,193,1692]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURES 126 – 140. Female genitalia of Istrianis species, sternite VIII. 126 — I. lvovskyi, PT, Mongolia (gen. slide 61 / 10, O. Bidzilya); 127 — I. lvovskyi, PT, Mongolia (gen. slide 253 / 12, O. Bidzilya); 128 — I. sruogai, HT, Tadzhikistan (gen. slide 175 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 129 — I. sruogai, Turkmenistan (gen. slide 178 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 130 — I. piskunovi, PT, Ukraine (gen. slide 92 / 11, O. Bidzilya); 131 — I. falkovitshi, PT, Turkmenistan (gen. slide 10 / 13, O. Bidzilya); 132 — I. squamodorella, PT, Palestine (gen. slide 26 / 11, O. Bidzilya); 133 — I. squamodorella, Pakistan (B. M. gen. slide 14354); 134 — I. squamodorella, Pakistan (gen. slide 418 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 135 — I. nigrosquamella, PT, Iran (gen. slide 318 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 136 — I. nigrosquamella, Iraq (gen. slide 407 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 137 — I. kyrgyzsquamella, PT, Kazakhstan (gen. slide 259 / 12, O. Bidzilya); 138 — I. kyrgyzsquamella, PT, Kyrgyzstan (gen. slide 59 / 11, O. Bidzilya); 139 — I. yemeniasquamella, PT, Yemen (gen. slide 261 / 14, O. Bidzilya); 140 — I. yemeniasquamella, PT, Yemen (gen. slide 157 / 14, O. Bidzilya)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/237411/files/figure.png" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">131</figureCitation>
). Segment VIII nearly as long as broad; apophyses anteriores nearly two times longer than segment VIII; anterior margin with elongated lobes; posterior sclerite very narrow, much broader than long; anterolateral sclerites narrow, horn-shaped; anterior sclerites digitate, narrow; antrum tubular; ductus bursae moderately long; corpus bursae rounded; signum subhexagonal, posterior lobe with nearly straight upper margin, anterior lobe slightly broader than posterior lobe, with deep medial emargination, medial ridge moderately broad.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="34" pageNumber="435" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="34.[151,1437,582,1867]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1482,1507]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[334,480,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falkovitshi">
<emphasis box="[334,480,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">I. falkovitshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is externally similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[774,910,1482,1507]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piskunovi">
<emphasis box="[774,910,1482,1507]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">I. piskunovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the forewings are darker, and the male hindwings are mottled with brown. The male genitalia are very similar to those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1111,1244,1518,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piskunovi">
<emphasis box="[1111,1244,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">I. piskunovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differ in the narrower, medially constricted (parallel-sided in 
<taxonomicName box="[699,830,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="piskunovi">
<emphasis box="[699,830,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">I. piskunovi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) lateral lobes of tegumen; moreover the anteromedial emargination of tegumen is deeper than in the related species; sternite VIII that is more than two times longer than broad is an additional diagnostic character of 
<taxonomicName box="[684,827,1626,1651]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falkovitshi">
<emphasis box="[684,827,1626,1651]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">I. falkovitshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A very narrow horn-shaped anterolateral sclerite in combination with the very small posterior sclerite are characters that reliable separate the female genitalia of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falkovitshi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">I. falkovitshi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the rest of 
<taxonomicName box="[455,548,1700,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Gelechiidae" genus="Istrianis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[455,548,1700,1723]" italics="true" pageId="34" pageNumber="435">Istrianis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1117,1734,1759]" pageId="34" pageNumber="435" type="biology_ecology">
